The paper proposes a novel supervised feature learning technique for classification based on error representation learning. This involves learning the representation of error as high-level features, which can be particularly effective in data sets with diverse feature representations or imbalanced classes. This approach is related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, given the focus on feature learning and classification, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
